  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-02-25",
    "date": "2025-05-07T19:05:50Z",
    "text": "Stop Sexual Harassment in K-12 Act\n\nThis bill outlines the role and duties of Title IX coordinators in elementary and secondary schools, including by requiring local educational agencies to increase the number of full-time employees designated to serve as a Title IX coordinator per specified student population. The bill also creates a grant program to train teachers and staff on how to respond to signs of sex-based\u00a0harassment and assault of students and requires the Department of Education to develop a sex-based harassment\u00a0survey."
